The paper deals with the algebraic approach to the theory of databases, specifically the use of lattice theory to study the natural join and inner union operations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the undecidability of certain problems, which is a common theme in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. The use of lattice theory to study databases also suggests a connection to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of quasiequations, which are a tool commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
